WEBVTT

00:17.230 --> 00:20.552
Captions made possible by
HOME BOX OFFICE

00:20.560 --> 00:24.599
A Division of TIME WARNER
ENTERTAINMENT COMPANY, LP.

01:56.600 --> 02:00.821
( female )
PIKE PLACE MARKET WAS BORN
IN 1907 FROM CITIZEN OUTRAGE

02:00.830 --> 02:03.219
AT THE HIGH COST
OF PRODUCE,

02:03.230 --> 02:05.824
WHEN SEATTLE CITY
COUNCILMAN THOMAS REVELLE

02:05.830 --> 02:07.695
PROPOSED A PUBLIC
STREET MARKET.

02:07.700 --> 02:10.749
ON OPENING DAY,
AUGUST 7th, 1907,

02:10.760 --> 02:14.252
EIGHT FARMERS
BROUGHT THEIR WAGONS

02:14.260 --> 02:15.989
TO THE CORNER
OF FIRST AND PIKE

02:16.000 --> 02:19.754
AND WERE OVERWHELMED BY AN
ESTIMATED 10,000 EAGER SHOPPERS.

02:19.760 --> 02:22.854
BY 11 AM. THEY WERE
COMPLETELY SOLD OUT.

02:24.530 --> 02:26.725
WELL, THAT CONCLUDES
THE MORNING HALF OF OUR TOUR.

02:26.730 --> 02:27.924
ONCE AGAIN,

02:27.930 --> 02:29.227
MY NAME'S KAREN,

02:29.230 --> 02:31.255
AND YOU'VE JUST BEEN
A SUPER-DUPER GROUP
THIS MORNING

02:31.260 --> 02:32.921
AND WE'LL SEE YOU
BACK HERE ON THE BUS

02:32.930 --> 02:34.693
AT HALF PAST
1:00.

02:37.730 --> 02:38.754
I DON'T KNOW
ABOUT YOU,

02:38.760 --> 02:40.193
BUT I COULD SURE
USE A FUCKING CIGARETTE.

02:40.200 --> 02:41.258
THANK YOU,
KAREN.

02:46.030 --> 02:47.850
OKAY, BYE.

02:50.930 --> 02:53.148
EXCUSE ME, SIR ?

02:55.160 --> 02:58.425
Sir, it's lunchtime,
you can get off the bus now.

02:58.430 --> 02:59.727
We're at
Pike Place Market !

02:59.730 --> 03:01.994
SIR !

03:09.630 --> 03:11.029
SHIT.

03:11.030 --> 03:15.194
WE'VE GOT ANOTHER DEAD ONE
BACK HERE, LARRY.

03:17.630 --> 03:20.053
( horns blaring )

03:29.730 --> 03:32.528
YOU'VE MISSED
YOUR LAST THREE SESSIONS.

03:32.530 --> 03:33.656
YEAH, WELL.

03:33.660 --> 03:35.321
SOMETIMES COMING IN HERE
TALKING ABOUT MY LIFE

03:35.330 --> 03:36.991
GETS IN THE WAY
OF ME HAVING ONE.

03:37.000 --> 03:39.958
SO, WHY'D YOU BOTHER
COMING IN TODAY THEN ?

03:39.960 --> 03:42.292
BECAUSE THEY SENT A LETTER
TO MY MOTHER

03:42.300 --> 03:44.996
AND THREATENED
TO SUSPEND ME IF I DIDN'T.

03:46.460 --> 03:48.098
I THOUGHT MAYBE
YOU HAD SOMETHING

03:48.100 --> 03:49.351
YOU WANTED
TO TALK ABOUT.

03:49.360 --> 03:50.349
WITH YOU ?

03:50.360 --> 03:51.497
YEAH, RIGHT.

03:51.500 --> 03:54.253
ARE YOU ANGRY
WITH ME ?

03:54.260 --> 03:57.229
HOW CAN YOU TELL ?

03:59.000 --> 04:01.594
I WAS OBLIGATED TO COOPERATE
WITH THE POLICE, CLAIRE.

04:01.600 --> 04:03.329
IT'S MY JOB.

04:03.330 --> 04:05.355
AND JUST SO YOU KNOW,
I WAS HERE FOR YOU,
NOT FOR THEM.

04:05.360 --> 04:07.726
THEY WANTED
TO INTERROGATE YOU ALONE.

04:07.730 --> 04:10.153
AND THEY HAVEN'T
FOUND HIM YET.

04:10.160 --> 04:11.718
IN CASE YOU'RE...

04:11.730 --> 04:12.924
CURIOUS.

04:12.930 --> 04:14.955
WELL, I'M NOT.

04:16.830 --> 04:18.229
YOU HAVEN'T
HEARD FROM HIM ?

04:18.230 --> 04:19.652
FUCK, NO !

04:19.660 --> 04:21.696
NOT THAT
I'D TELL YOU IF I HAD.

04:21.700 --> 04:23.099
FOR THE RECORD,
YOU DID THE RIGHT THING

04:23.100 --> 04:24.658
WHEN YOU CALLED THE POLICE
THAT NIGHT, CLAIRE.

04:24.660 --> 04:26.059
I KNOW I DID
THE RIGHT THING.

04:27.760 --> 04:29.250
I DID THE RIGHT
FUCKING THING.

04:29.260 --> 04:30.921
GIVEN THE CIRCUMSTANCES,
IT'S COMPLETELY UNDERSTANDABLE

04:30.930 --> 04:32.727
THAT YOU'RE FEELING
THIS ANGRY, CLAIRE.

04:32.730 --> 04:35.358
IF YOU DON'T STOP
SAYING MY NAME

04:35.360 --> 04:37.555
AT THE END OF EVERY SENTENCE,
I'M GONNA--

04:37.560 --> 04:38.356
WHAT ?

04:38.360 --> 04:40.123
I DON'T KNOW.

04:41.430 --> 04:42.658
JUST DON'T...

04:42.660 --> 04:44.651
OKAY ?

04:49.900 --> 04:51.595
YOU FEEL LIKE
THROWING SOMETHING ?

04:51.600 --> 04:53.818
EXCUSE ME ?

04:53.830 --> 04:55.457
YOU COULD, YOU KNOW,

04:55.460 --> 04:57.758
JUST PICK SOMETHING UP
OFF MY DESK AND CHUCK IT.

04:57.760 --> 05:01.298
I'M SO SURE YOU'D LET ME
TRASH SOMETHING OFF YOUR DESK.

05:01.300 --> 05:03.325
IF YOU THOUGHT
IT MIGHT HELP, I WOULD.

05:14.700 --> 05:17.555
NO, THANKS.

05:19.200 --> 05:20.656
YOU'RE ANGRY WITH GABE

05:20.660 --> 05:22.389
AND YOU'RE SCARED

05:22.400 --> 05:24.698
BECAUSE YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN TO HIM.

05:26.060 --> 05:29.393
AT THIS POINT, I DON'T GIVE
A FLYING FUCK ABOUT HIM.

05:29.400 --> 05:32.528
YOU DON'T REALLY
FEEL THAT WAY, DO YOU ?

05:34.230 --> 05:35.857
NO.

05:55.360 --> 05:57.590
I DO FEEL BETTER,
THANK YOU.

05:59.930 --> 06:02.023
HE WAS ON
ONE OF THOSE...

06:02.030 --> 06:03.759
PACKAGE BUS TOURS.

06:03.760 --> 06:05.489
HE'D BEEN GOING
ON THEM A LOT,

06:05.500 --> 06:07.491
THREE OR FOUR TIMES A YEAR
EVER SINCE MOM DIED.

06:07.500 --> 06:09.752
SOMETIMES HE WENT
WITH HIS FRIEND, PETE.

06:09.760 --> 06:11.899
THIS TIME
HE WENT ALONE.

06:11.900 --> 06:15.825
THEY THINK HIS HEART
JUST GAVE OUT.

06:17.160 --> 06:18.821
I'M VERY SORRY.

06:18.830 --> 06:21.390
AND WHERE IS
YOUR FATHER NOW ?

06:21.400 --> 06:25.325
HE'S STILL UP THERE
IN SEATTLE.

06:26.300 --> 06:28.427
THE COLUMBIA FUNERAL HOME'S
HOLDING HIM FOR US.

06:28.430 --> 06:29.692
THEY'RE ON
RAINIER AVENUE.

06:29.700 --> 06:31.292
NOT A PROBLEM.

06:31.300 --> 06:33.951
WE CAN MAKE ARRANGEMENTS
TO HAVE HIM FLOWN BACK TO L.A.

06:37.030 --> 06:38.588
FLOWN BACK ?

06:38.600 --> 06:39.749
YES.

06:39.760 --> 06:41.091
DAD WON'T FLY.

06:41.100 --> 06:44.092
IT WAS ALWAYS A SORE SPOT
WITH MOM.

06:44.100 --> 06:47.126
SHE WANTED TO TRAVEL,
BUT DAD FLAT OUT REFUSED.

06:47.130 --> 06:49.257
AND THEN,
AFTER SHE DIED,

06:49.260 --> 06:52.127
HE STARTED TAKING ALL
THESE PACKAGE BUS TOURS.

06:52.130 --> 06:53.392
HE HAS...

06:53.400 --> 06:56.654
HAD A THING
ABOUT FLYING.

06:56.660 --> 06:57.957
HE NEVER FLEW.

06:57.960 --> 07:00.224
I'M SURE,
GIVEN THE CIRCUMSTANCES--

07:00.230 --> 07:02.323
NO, IT ISN'T WHAT
HE WOULD'VE WANTED.

07:02.330 --> 07:05.322
ISN'T THERE
SOME OTHER WAY ?

07:07.300 --> 07:09.120
WE CAN MAKE ARRANGEMENTS
TO HAVE HIM SHIPPED,

07:09.130 --> 07:11.348
VIA RAIL OR FREIGHT.

07:12.500 --> 07:14.058
LIKE FED-EX ?

07:14.060 --> 07:15.891
YOU CAN DO THAT ?

07:15.900 --> 07:17.527
IT'S DONE
ALL THE TIME.

07:17.530 --> 07:20.397
THEY BROUGHT ABRAHAM LINCOLN
HOME TO ILLINOIS BY TRAIN

07:20.400 --> 07:23.699
ALL THE WAY FROM WASHINGTON,
PACKED IN ICE.

07:29.360 --> 07:31.828
IT SHOULDN'T
BE A PROBLEM.

07:34.700 --> 07:36.224
NOW, KEITH,
I'LL BE BACK UP HERE

07:36.230 --> 07:37.925
JUST AS SOON AS YOUR FATHER'S
BACK ON HIS FEET.

07:37.930 --> 07:40.125
WHAT IF GRANDPA DIES ?

07:40.130 --> 07:44.351
MY FRIEND NEISHA'S BROTHER
HAD AN OPERATION AND HE DIED.

07:44.360 --> 07:48.023
I TOLD YOU, TAYLOR,
IT'S JUST A HERNIA.

07:48.030 --> 07:49.588
IT'S NOTHING FOR YOU
TO WORRY ABOUT.

07:49.600 --> 07:52.023
I'D SURE LIKE TO KNOW
WHERE THE HELL KARLA IS.

07:52.030 --> 07:55.295
SHE STILL UP IN OAKLAND
WITH DERRICK ?

07:57.530 --> 07:59.998
DID SHE EVEN OFFER
TO COME BACK DOWN HERE

08:00.000 --> 08:01.956
AND TAKE CARE OF HER KID WHEN
YOU TOLD HER YOU WERE LEAVING ?

08:01.960 --> 08:05.350
WE HAVEN'T
HEARD FROM HER.

08:07.660 --> 08:09.218
JESUS.

08:10.460 --> 08:12.451
I THOUGHT YOU HAD
A NUMBER FOR HER.

08:14.130 --> 08:15.552
IT'S BEEN DISCONNECTED.

08:15.560 --> 08:16.492
OH, SHIT !

08:16.500 --> 08:18.092
I TOLD YOU, KEITH,

08:18.100 --> 08:20.091
HUSH THAT KIND OF MOUTH
AROUND YOUR NIECE !

08:20.100 --> 08:23.399
MAYBE I SHOULD JUST
TAKE THE CHILD WITH ME.

08:23.400 --> 08:25.789
LOOK, SHE'LL BE FINE,
ALRIGHT ?

08:25.800 --> 08:28.724
MY NEW PLACE HAS AN EXTRA ROOM,
AND BETWEEN EDDIE AND ME,

08:28.730 --> 08:30.493
WE'LL MAKE SURE SHE'S--

08:30.500 --> 08:31.899
I DON'T WANT
TO COME STAY WITH YOU.

08:31.900 --> 08:33.754
HOW COME YOU CAN'T
COME STAY HERE ?

08:33.760 --> 08:35.296
BECAUSE MY THINGS
ARE AT MY PLACE.

08:35.300 --> 08:36.927
WHAT ABOUT MY STUFF ?

08:36.930 --> 08:38.591
YOU CAN BRING IT
WITH YOU.

08:38.600 --> 08:40.329
UH-UH, YOU'D
PROBABLY STEAL IT.

08:40.330 --> 08:41.729
( horn honking )

08:41.730 --> 08:43.129
THERE'S MY CAB.

08:43.130 --> 08:46.497
TAYLOR, COME ON, HONEY,
GIVE YOUR GRANDMA A HUG.

08:52.230 --> 08:54.255
I LOVE YOU,
GRAN DMA.

08:54.260 --> 08:55.898
NOW, YOU BE GOOD.

08:55.900 --> 08:59.392
AND YOU MIND
YOUR UNCLE KEITH.

09:01.130 --> 09:03.496
I'LL TRY TO COME BACK
AS FAST AS I CAN.

09:14.800 --> 09:17.758
I KNOW A LOT WORSER WORDS
THAN "SHIT", YOU KNOW.

09:17.760 --> 09:20.058
SO DO I.

09:25.960 --> 09:28.099
SO, HOW'D THE MOSSBACK
INTAKE GO ?

09:28.100 --> 09:30.421
WE NEED TO COME UP WITH A WAY
TO GET A BODY SHIPPED BACK

09:30.430 --> 09:31.988
FROM YOUR OLD
STOMPING GROUND.

09:32.000 --> 09:33.524
WHY CAN'T
YOU JUST FLY IT BACK ?

09:33.530 --> 09:35.657
THAT'S WHAT YOUR FATHER
ALWAYS DID.

09:35.660 --> 09:37.491
APPARENTLY THE DECEASED
WAS AFRAID OF FLYING.

09:37.500 --> 09:39.456
I DON'T THINK HE'S GONNA
GIVE A SHIT NOW, DAVID.

09:39.460 --> 09:41.519
THE FAMILY DOESN'T
WANT HIM TO FLY.

09:41.530 --> 09:44.499
AND THE FREIGHT COMPANIES
ARE BACKED UP UNTIL NEXT WEEK,

09:44.500 --> 09:47.025
AND AMTRAK CAN'T BRING HIM
BACK UNTIL NEXT TUESDAY.

09:47.030 --> 09:49.157
NO PROBLEM.

09:49.160 --> 09:52.425
I'LL FLY UP,
RENT A REFRIGERATED VAN,
DRIVE HIM BACK.

09:52.430 --> 09:54.648
YOU DON'T NEED
A REFRIGERATED VAN,

09:54.660 --> 09:56.196
JUST A ONE-WAY RENTAL.

09:56.200 --> 09:57.497
HE'S ALREADY
BEEN EMBALMED.

09:57.500 --> 09:58.853
EVEN EASIER.

09:58.860 --> 10:00.327
YOU'D DO THAT ?

10:00.330 --> 10:02.719
FLY UP THERE, TURN AROUND
AND DRIVE ALL THE WAY BACK ?

10:02.730 --> 10:04.049
SURE.

10:04.060 --> 10:05.254
I HAVEN'T BEEN BACK
SINCE CHRISTMAS,

10:05.260 --> 10:06.397
I CAN SEE
A FEW OF FRIENDS.

10:06.400 --> 10:07.958
I STILL HAVE SOME STUFF
UP THERE, I'D LOVE TO.

10:07.960 --> 10:09.757
I SUPPOSE WE COULD
MARK UP THE COST OF SHIPPING

10:09.760 --> 10:10.988
TO COVER YOUR TRAVEL.

10:11.000 --> 10:12.228
WHEN DO YOU
WANT ME TO LEAVE ?

10:12.230 --> 10:13.356
TOMORROW ?

10:13.360 --> 10:14.793
DONE.

10:20.730 --> 10:23.494
HAVE YOU MET ANY NICE MEN
RECENTLY, DAVID ?

10:25.460 --> 10:27.325
NO ONE TO SPEAK OF.

10:27.330 --> 10:29.855
WELL, I WISH YOU'D
PUT YOURSELF OUT MORE.

10:29.860 --> 10:33.296
THE DOOR TO YOUR HOUSE ONLY
OPENS FROM THE INSIDE, YOU KNOW.

10:33.300 --> 10:35.894
( laughing )

10:35.900 --> 10:38.050
WE HAVEN'T SEEN
YOUR FRIEND, GABRIEL

10:38.060 --> 10:39.357
AROUND MUCH LATELY,
CLAIRE.

10:39.360 --> 10:41.191
SO?

10:41.200 --> 10:43.657
HAVE YOU NOT BEEN
SEEING AS MUCH OF HIM ?

10:43.660 --> 10:45.389
NO, I HAVEN'T.

10:45.400 --> 10:47.425
DID YOU TWO
HAVE A FALLING OUT ?

10:47.430 --> 10:49.819
YEAH, GABE JOINED
THE HARE KRISHNA, OKAY ?

10:49.830 --> 10:52.924
THOSE PEOPLE
WITH THE ORANGE ROBES
AND TAMBOURINES ?

10:52.930 --> 10:56.388
THAT TRY TO SELL YOU
BOOKS IN THE AIRPORT,
YEP, THAT'S THEM.

10:56.400 --> 10:59.221
OH, MY GOODNESS.

10:59.230 --> 11:02.256
HE NEVER STRUCK ME
AS A RELIGIOUS PERSON.

11:02.260 --> 11:04.455
WELL, HE IS NOW,
BIG TIME.

11:04.460 --> 11:06.223
DID HE SHAVE
HIS HEAD ?

11:06.230 --> 11:07.549
YEAH, HE SHAVED
HIS HEAD.

11:07.560 --> 11:10.393
CAN WE TALK ABOUT
SOMETHING ELSE, PLEASE ?

11:12.060 --> 11:15.223
CLAIRE, YOU WANNA COME UP
TO SEATTLE WITH ME ?

11:16.930 --> 11:19.490
YOU'RE ASKING ME TO COME
TO SEATTLE WITH YOU ?

11:19.500 --> 11:20.990
YEAH, WHY NOT ?

11:21.000 --> 11:23.059
I'M NOT SURE WE CAN
STICK THE MOSSBACKS

11:23.060 --> 11:24.596
WITH ANOTHER
PLANE TICKET, NATE.

11:24.600 --> 11:25.658
I'LL PAY FOR IT.

11:25.660 --> 11:27.218
YEAH.
YOU WILL ?

11:27.230 --> 11:28.458
I COULD USE THE COMPANY,
AND BESIDES,

11:28.460 --> 11:30.348
YOU CAN HELP WITH SOME
OF THE DRIVING ON THE WAY BACK.

11:30.360 --> 11:31.759
SHE'LL MISS SCHOOL.

11:31.760 --> 11:33.398
WE'RE NOT DOING ANYTHING
IN CLASS I CAN'T MISS,

11:33.400 --> 11:34.753
AND I CAN BRING
MY HOMEWORK WITH ME.

11:34.760 --> 11:36.796
IT'S JUST FOR
A COUPLE OF DAYS.

11:39.060 --> 11:40.596
FINE.

11:40.600 --> 11:43.421
I'M TIRED OF TRYING TO BE
THE ARCHITECT FOR THIS FAMILY.

11:43.430 --> 11:46.991
IT'S HIGH TIME YOU DREW
YOUR OWN BLUEPRINTS.

11:55.830 --> 11:58.822
DOES ANYONE KNOW WHAT THE FUCK
SHE'S TALKING ABOUT ANYMORE ?

12:01.900 --> 12:04.528
WHAT ?
NATE.

12:10.330 --> 12:12.150
( urinating )
OH, HEY,
BY THE WAY,

12:12.160 --> 12:13.627
I'M FLYING UP
TO SEATTLE TOMORROW.

12:13.630 --> 12:15.154
YOU ARE ?

12:15.160 --> 12:16.354
YEAH.

12:16.360 --> 12:19.852
I'M PICKING UP A BODY
AND DRIVING IT BACK FOR DAVID.

12:19.860 --> 12:22.328
I'M GONNA
TAKE CLAIRE WITH ME.

12:22.330 --> 12:24.059
SOUNDS LIKE FUN.

12:26.030 --> 12:27.520
YOU DON'T MIND
THAT I DIDN'T ASK YOU ?

12:29.360 --> 12:30.793
TO GO WITH ME.

12:30.800 --> 12:33.394
NO, NOT AT ALL.

12:33.400 --> 12:35.391
GOOD.

12:37.200 --> 12:38.690
YOU SURE ?

12:38.700 --> 12:41.419
NATE, I'M TRYING
TO READ.

12:41.430 --> 12:44.297
AND YOU KNOW I HATE IT
WHEN YOU FLOSS IN FRONT OF ME.

12:46.500 --> 12:47.922
SORRY.

12:51.400 --> 12:52.753
IS IT WEIRD
THAT I DIDN'T ASK YOU

12:52.760 --> 12:54.318
TO COME UP
TO SEATTLE WITH ME ?

12:54.330 --> 12:56.195
NO, WHY WOULD IT BE ?

12:56.200 --> 12:57.952
I DON'T KNOW.

12:57.960 --> 12:59.222
IT JUST FEELS
A LITTLE WEIRD.

12:59.230 --> 13:01.255
OKAY, NOW IT IS
A LITTLE WEIRD.

13:01.260 --> 13:03.399
BUT ONLY BECAUSE YOU'RE
MAKING IT A LITTLE WEIRD.

13:03.400 --> 13:05.152
BUT YOU'RE NOT
MAD ABOUT IT ?

13:05.160 --> 13:06.491
NOT AT ALL.

13:06.500 --> 13:08.422
I THINK IT'S REALLY
GOOD FOR YOU

13:08.430 --> 13:09.920
TO SPEND SOME TIME
WITH YOUR SISTER.

13:09.930 --> 13:11.955
THAT'S WHAT I THINK.

13:24.830 --> 13:26.127
YOU SURE
IT'S NOT TOO WEIRD ?

13:26.130 --> 13:28.951
OH GOD, NATE,
GIVE IT A REST.

13:30.600 --> 13:31.749
GOODNIGHT, BREN.

13:31.760 --> 13:32.897
GOODNIGHT.

14:00.560 --> 14:03.290
COOL, SLEATER-KINNEY'S
PLAYING AT THIS PLACE

14:03.300 --> 14:04.927
CALLED SHOWBOX TONIGHT.

14:04.930 --> 14:07.626
I HATE TO BREAK IT TO YOU,
BUT SHOWBOX IS 18 AND OVER.

14:07.630 --> 14:10.827
WHAT MAKES YOU THINK
I DON'T HAVE A FAKE I.D. ?

14:10.830 --> 14:13.321
YOU HAVE A FAKE I.D. ?

14:13.330 --> 14:16.424
YOU'RE NOT GONNA PULL SOME
PSEUDO-PARENTAL BULLSHIT

14:16.430 --> 14:17.852
ON ME, ARE YOU ?

14:17.860 --> 14:19.020
NO.

14:19.030 --> 14:20.895
I HAD A FAKE I.D.
ONCE, TOO.

14:20.900 --> 14:23.027
MAYBE I'LL
GO WITH YOU.

14:23.030 --> 14:25.555
I DON'T NEED
A BABY-SITTER, NATE.

14:25.560 --> 14:27.152
I LOVE SLEATER-KINNEY.

14:27.160 --> 14:30.129
YOU LOVE
SLEATER-KINNEY ?

14:32.400 --> 14:33.890
WOULD YOU JUST TRY TO GET
OVER YOURSELF FOR A SECOND

14:33.900 --> 14:36.323
AND LET ME BE YOUR FRIEND
AND YOUR BROTHER ?

14:41.660 --> 14:42.854
DID YOU BRING ME
ON THIS TRIP

14:42.860 --> 14:44.725
BECAUSE YOU THOUGHT I NEEDED
A LITTLE DISTRACT ION ?

14:44.730 --> 14:47.551
NO, I INVITED YOU ON THIS TRIP
BECAUSE I THOUGHT IT'D BE FUN

14:47.560 --> 14:49.152
TO BRING YOU ALONG.

14:49.160 --> 14:51.219
NOW I'M HAVING
SECOND THOUGHTS.

14:51.230 --> 14:52.356
OKAY.

14:52.360 --> 14:53.497
OKAY ?

14:53.500 --> 14:55.991
I BELIEVE YOU.

14:58.960 --> 15:01.019
SO, LIKE, WHERE ARE
WE STAYING ANYWAY ?

15:01.030 --> 15:02.622
MY FRIEND LISA'S.

15:02.630 --> 15:04.120
SHE AN OLD GIRLFRIEND ?

15:04.130 --> 15:05.449
NO.

15:05.460 --> 15:07.394
NO WAY,
NOT EVEN CLOSE.

15:07.400 --> 15:10.949
WE WERE STRICTLY ROOMMATES,
NOTHING MORE.

15:10.960 --> 15:13.428
WORKED AT
THE CO-OP TOGETHER.

15:15.730 --> 15:18.619
IS SHE ALL CRUNCHY GRANOLA,
BACK-PACKY

15:18.630 --> 15:20.894
AND WAY INTO GRUNGE ?

15:20.900 --> 15:23.391
UM, CRUNCHY GRANOLA,

15:23.400 --> 15:25.027
MAYBE A LITTLE.

15:25.030 --> 15:26.395
BACK-PACKY,
DEFINITELY.

15:26.400 --> 15:28.493
INTO GRUNGE ?
NO WAY.

15:28.500 --> 15:31.094
GRUNGE DIED LONG BEFORE
KURT COBAIN DID.

15:31.100 --> 15:33.125
BESIDES, LISA IS...

15:33.130 --> 15:37.499
NOT SO EASY
TO CATEGORIZE.

15:40.800 --> 15:42.552
YOU GUYS DID IT A FEW TIMES,
THOUGH, RIGHT ?

15:42.560 --> 15:43.891
WE'RE NOT HAVING
THIS DISCUSSION.

15:43.900 --> 15:45.219
FINE.

16:02.400 --> 16:04.857
WELL, THIS IS IT.

16:06.260 --> 16:07.522
SWEET.

16:25.460 --> 16:27.951
I REMEMBER
A SUMMER'S DAY

16:31.760 --> 16:34.695
I REMEMBER
WALKING UP TO YOU

16:37.600 --> 16:40.194
I REMEMBER
MY FACE TURNED RED

16:42.000 --> 16:43.558
NATE !

